change.item: In 2000, Stacee Seager revised the organization and completed processing the collection under the supervision of Trevor James Bond. In 2018, Kaitlyn Van Vleet digitized all images as 1200 dpi tifs which have been placed in WSU MASC's archival storage.

did.abstract: Lantern slides were used for instructional and promotional purposes at WSU early in the century.

bioghist.p: Lantern slides were used for instructional and promotional purposes at WSU early in the century.

arrangement.p: The collection is organized into eight series: Buildings, Faculty, Students, Sports, Campus Events, Pullman Scenes, Landscapes, and Teaching Aids.

accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research use.

prefercite.p: [Item Description]. PC 6, W.S.U. Lantern Slides. Manuscripts, Archives, and Special Collections, Washington State University Libraries, Pullman, WA.

acqinfo.p: The bulk of the WSU lantern slides were donated to the Washington State University Library by Dr. Al Butler. The donors of the rest of the collection are not accounted for.

controlaccess.p: This collection is indexed under the following headings in the online catalog. Researchers desiring materials about related topics, persons, or places should search the catalog using these headings.

dsc.p: The following section contains a detailed listing of the materials in the collection.
